         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Somerset Place, Norwood ¶ 25th Feb. 1885. ¶ Most esteemed Baron! ¶  ¶ I have taken the liberty again to send off a packet of specimens with today’s post for determination, if you will be so kind as to...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">85.02.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS is bound into an inscribed copy of Tepper (1886).</p>
               </note>Somerset Place, Norwood</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">25th Feb. 1885.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochverehetester Hr. Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit heutigen Post bin ich wieder so frei gewesen, ein Packet Spezimen zur Bestimmung abzusenden, wenn Sie so gütig sein wollen, das dieses Mal, wie schon so oft, zu übernehmen. Die Pflanzen von Kangaroo Island sind mir von Mr. Horswill überbracht werden, der sie in der Nähe von Cape Willoughby gesammelt hat. Sie werden darunter einen Theil solcher Pflanzen bemerken, die ich auf m.Tour ohne Blüthen oder Früchte fand.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Ist es Ihnen schon bekannt, dass die Blätter von <name key="Drosera%20binata">Drosera binata</name> Wurtzel schlagen und eine Anzahl junger Pflänzchen produziren, wenn dieselben in fliessendes Wasser tauchen? Ich bemerkte dieses Ende Januar in Waterfall Gully u. wiess einiger Spezimen vor in letzter Sitzung unsrer Royal Society.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bitte, nehmen Sie freundlichst meinen herzlichen Dank entgegen für Ihre Aufmerksamkeit in Bezug auf die Zusendung Ihre Novitäten u. auch für die letzte Namenliste. Es ist aus Ihren erneuten Thätigkeiten zu schliessen, dass sich Ihre Gesundheit gebessert hat, u. hoffe ich, dass sie Ihnen recht lange erhalten bleiben möchte. — Welcher Spezies <name key="Melaleuca">Melaleuca</name> ist der hiesige Paper bark Teatree zuzuweisen?</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit herlichem Grusse habe ich die Ehre zu verbleiben</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ganz der Ihrige</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>JG Otto Tepper</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Baron Sir Ferd. von Muller K.C.M.G., DM &amp; Ph. D. F.R.S. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Govt. Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Victoria</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Somerset Place, Norwood<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Adelaide.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25th Feb. 1885.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Most esteemed Baron!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have taken the liberty again to send off a packet of specimens with today’s post for determination, if you will be so kind as to undertake it this time as so often before. The plants from Kangaroo Island<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>SA.</p>
               </note> have been brought over to me by Mr Horswill, who has collected them in the neighbourhood of Cape Willoughby. You will notice among them a part of such plants as I found on my tour without flowers or fruits.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is it already known to you that the leaves of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Drosera%20binata">Drosera binata</name>
               </seg> put down roots and produce a number of young plants if they are immersed in flowing water? I noticed this at the end of January in Waterfall Gully<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>SA.</p>
               </note> and showed some specimens at the last meeting of our Royal Society.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia</seg>, vol. 8 (1884-5), p. 165, report of the meeting of the Society on 5 February 1885: 'Mr. Tepper showed a new variety of Drosera'. The new 'variety' was probably <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. aphylla</seg>, not <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. binata</seg> which is also mentioned in Tepper (1885a) and in the summary in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Botanisches Centralblatt</seg>, vol. 27, p. 100 (1886).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please kindly accept my heartfelt thanks for your attention in regard to the sending of your new publications and also for the last list of names.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>List not identified.</p>
               </note> It is to be concluded from your renewed activity that your health has improved and I hope that it may be maintained for a long time. To what species of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Melaleuca">Melaleuca</name>
               </seg> is the local Paperbark Teatree assigned?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With sincere greeting I have the honour to remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J.G. Otto Tepper</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Sir Ferd. von Mueller K.C.M.G. M &amp; Ph.D., F.R.S. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Govt. Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Victoria</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Drosera%20binata">Drosera binata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Melaleuca">Melaleuca</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
